      "order": 5,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# 📌 ComfyUI Workflow Notes\n\n**Author:** Sharvin Suntoobacus\n\n**YouTube Channel:** [CodeCraftersCorner](https://www.youtube.com/@codecrafterscorner)\n\n**Patreon:** [Support on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/codecrafterscorner)\n\n---\n\n### ℹ️ About This Workflow\n\nThis workflow provides a streamlined setup for the **CyberRealistic Z-Image Turbo Catalyst** model. It features an automated **Resolution Master** system that ensures compatibility across various aspect ratios and banner formats. Users can achieve improved skin textures, refined color grading, and superior LoRA compatibility with high-speed generation (9 steps).\n\n### 🎥 Tutorial / Guide\n\nIf available, you can watch the video here:\n\n**[Watch on YouTube](https://youtu.be/nDm_rDyL3pM)**\n\n### 📥 Model Links (for Local Users)\n\n- **diffusion_models**\n    - [CyberRealistic Z-Image Turbo Catalyst](https://civitai.com/models/2513307/cyberrealistic-z-image-turbo-catalyst)\n        \n- **text_encoders**\n    - `qwen3_4b.safetensors` (for 16GB+ VRAM)\n    - `qwen34bfp8_scaled.safetensors` (for 8–12GB VRAM)\n        \n- **vae**\n    - `ae.safetensors` (required for all setups)\n        \n\n### 📂 Model Storage Location\n\nPlace the downloaded files into the following directories within your ComfyUI installation:\n\n📂 **ComfyUI/** \n\n\t├── 📂 **models/** \n\n\t\t├── 📂 **diffusion_models/**\n\n\t\t\t └── `CyberRealistic_Z_Image_Turbo_Catalyst.safetensors`\n\n\t├── 📂 **text_encoders/** \n\n\t\t└── `qwen3_4b.safetensors`\n\n\t└── 📂 **vae/** \n\n\t\t└── `ae.safetensors`\n\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Notes\n\n- **Custom Nodes:** You must install the **Resolution Master** custom node via the ComfyUI Manager for the resizing logic to function.\n    \n- **Experimental Branch:** This Catalyst version is an experimental track; if you encounter stability issues with specific LoRAs, consider reverting to the stable V0.7 or the mainline Z-Image Turbo.\n    \n- **Subgraphs:** To integrate this into your existing workflows, it is recommended to group the nodes into a subgraph for easier management.\n    \n\n**Credit:** Please credit Sharvin Suntoobacus and share YouTube Channel Code Crafters Corner when sharing this workflow.\n\n**Support:** Your support on Patreon helps me continue creating these guides!\n\n**🙏 Thank you for your support!**\n\n---\n"
